Headlines.Headline: After Shaky 2nd Quarter, REITs Up 4%, Beating Broader Equities

PARAGRAPH.#text: Real-estate stocks that were hot at the start of the year received a cold shoulder from investors during the spring, an indication of growing volatility in property stocks. The Dow Jones All REIT Equity Index, which tracks the stocks of 133 real-estate investment trusts, delivered a total return of 4% in the second quarter. That was down sharply from a total return of 10.5% in the first quarter and 15% in the fourth quarter of last year. REITs were poised to end the quarter relatively flat until a stock-market rally Friday--ignited after European leaders agreed on a plan to bolster support for troubled banks--allowed the REIT index to end the quarter with a modest gain and a stronger overall finish than the broader stock market.
